---
import Deck from '../layouts/Deck.astro';
import AboutStakater from '../components/slides/AboutStakater.astro';
import Partnership from '../components/slides/Partnership.astro';
---
<Deck title="Stakater | Partner Sales Executive" persona="Partner Sales Executive">

  <!-- 1. Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>
        Your Ecosystem Needs a<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Platform Growth Partner.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="color:#5a5668; font-weight:500; font-size:32px;">
        How Stakater drives co-sell pipeline through lifecycle ownership.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Partner sales people are busy. Get to the point — what this means for their pipeline number.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"What I want to show you is how Stakater generates co-sell pipeline that keeps regenerating — not a one-time project, not a single deal, but a continuous stream of expansion opportunities sourced from accounts that are already in your ecosystem. Let me show you how that works."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. About Stakater -->
  <AboutStakater />

  <!-- 3. Partnership -->
  <Partnership />

  <!-- 4. The Partner Gap -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>
        Delivery Partners Close Projects.<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Nobody Owns What Comes Next.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:80px; align-items:start;">

        <div style="padding:30px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#5a5668; margin-bottom:16px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Typical Partner Motion</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            Project scoped and staffed.<br/>
            Implementation delivered.<br/>
            Partner disengages.<br/>
            Expansion opportunities go unregistered.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:16px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">What Creates Pipeline</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            Long-term lifecycle ownership.<br/>
            Platform growth creates new deal moments.<br/>
            Every expansion is a registerable opportunity.<br/>
            Portfolio adoption = new SKUs = new revenue.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Stakater is the lifecycle partner that keeps <span class="highlight">pipeline alive.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">This framing should resonate — partner teams see partners disengage all the time. Don't be critical, be direct.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The standard partner motion closes the project and moves on. That's not a criticism — that's how most delivery partners are built. But it means that once the implementation is done, the account goes quiet. No one is sourcing expansion opportunities. No one is registering deals. The ARR potential is there — it's just invisible because nobody's in the account. Stakater stays in the account. That's the difference."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Co-Sell Motion -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        The <span class="highlight">Co-Sell Motion</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:50px; text-align:center;">

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:16px;">Source</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            We identify expansion opportunities inside existing Red Hat accounts through lifecycle engagement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:16px;">Influence</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            We create technical demand — workload acceleration, portfolio readiness, governance alignment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:16px;">Register</h2>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            We co-register expansion deals — nodes, additional clusters, new Red Hat products.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        You set the commercial motion. We bring <span class="highlight">technical depth and account continuity.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">These three words — Source, Influence, Register — are partner program language. Use them intentionally.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Source, influence, register — the three verbs that matter in a co-sell program. We source opportunities by being in the account, continuously, managing the platform. We influence by creating the technical conditions that make expansion natural — more workloads, governance maturity, portfolio readiness. And we register — every node expansion, every new cluster, every additional product is a deal moment we bring to you. You own the commercial motion. We bring the technical depth and the account continuity."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Partner Credentials -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        A <span class="highlight">Credentialed</span> Co-Sell Partner
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:40px; text-align:center;">

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:26px; margin-bottom:14px;">CCSP</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Certified Cloud & Service Provider. Lifecycle management and managed OpenShift delivery.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:26px; margin-bottom:14px;">Specialized</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Container Management specialization. Recognized technical depth in OpenShift platforms.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:26px; margin-bottom:14px;">Certified Engineers</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">RHCEs and OpenShift specialists. Platform-native engineers, not generalists.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:26px; margin-bottom:14px;">8+ Years</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">In the Red Hat ecosystem. Progressive partner tier. Deep institutional alignment.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        Not a new partner. A <span class="highlight">proven ecosystem player.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">These credentials reduce partner-side risk. Emphasize that Stakater is a known quantity in the ecosystem.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Before you co-register with a partner, you want to know they can deliver. CCSP — lifecycle management and hosted OpenShift. Container Management Specialization — recognized technical depth. RHCEs and OpenShift-certified engineers on the team. Eight years in the ecosystem, progressive partner tier progression. This is not a new name. If you run the certification check, we'll be there."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. Joint Pipeline Play -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        The <span class="highlight">Joint Pipeline</span> Play
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:50px;">

        <div style="padding:36px; background:white; border-radius:12px; box-shadow:0 8px 30px rgba(26,13,50,0.07);">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:20px; font-size:22px;">Long-Term Account Continuity</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Stakater stays engaged after delivery. Every platform milestone — more workloads, new team onboarded, new compliance requirement — becomes a deal moment for the channel.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; background:white; border-radius:12px; box-shadow:0 8px 30px rgba(26,13,50,0.07);">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:20px; font-size:22px;">Proof: Multi-Year Partnerships</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            ATG: 7-year account. Continuous node growth.<br/><br/>
            CSN: Post-delivery → ODF adoption + expansion.<br/><br/>
            Region Skåne: Single cluster → org-wide standard.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        Every year Stakater is engaged, your pipeline <span class="highlight">keeps regenerating.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">The key phrase is "keeps regenerating." Pipeline from a single account over multiple years — that's the model.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The commercial insight here is compounding pipeline. Most partner relationships generate one deal per account. We generate deal moments continuously. Every new workload is a node expansion conversation. Every new team onboarding is a governance conversation. Every compliance milestone is a security product conversation. ATG has been generating registerable opportunities for seven years from a single account. CSN added ODF after delivery was done. Region Skåne is still expanding. That's the pipeline model."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. How to Engage -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        How to <span class="highlight">Engage Stakater</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:0; align-items:start; text-align:center;">

        <div style="padding:30px;">
          <div style="font-size:44px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px;">1</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:19px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px;">Identify</h3>
          <p style="font-size:16px; color:#1A0D32;">An account with a lifecycle gap — flat nodes, no portfolio adoption, delivery team gone.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px;">
          <div style="font-size:44px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px;">2</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:19px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px;">Introduce</h3>
          <p style="font-size:16px; color:#1A0D32;">Stakater for a platform assessment. We map the expansion opportunity together.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px;">
          <div style="font-size:44px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px;">3</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:19px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px;">Co-Design</h3>
          <p style="font-size:16px; color:#1A0D32;">Expansion strategy — workloads, products, clusters. Built jointly with your channel team.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px;">
          <div style="font-size:44px; font-weight:800; color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:14px;">4</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:19px; font-weight:600; margin-bottom:12px;">Register</h3>
          <p style="font-size:16px; color:#1A0D32;">Co-register the expansion deal — nodes, new products, additional clusters.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Walk through each step. Step 4 is the payoff — make sure it lands.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Four steps, no complexity. One — identify an account in your portfolio with a lifecycle gap. Flat nodes, no portfolio adoption, delivery partner already gone. Two — introduce Stakater for a platform assessment. We map the expansion opportunity jointly. Three — co-design the expansion strategy together. Workloads, products, clusters, roadmap. Four — co-register the deal. Nodes, new products, additional clusters — all registerable. You bring the account. We bring the lifecycle motion."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>Let's Build a Joint Pipeline.</h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Identify three accounts with a lifecycle gap.<br/>
        We'll show you where the pipeline is.
      </h2>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h1 style="font-weight:800;">Co-Sell. Co-Grow. Long-Term.</h1>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Clean close. The ask is low friction — make that explicit.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The starting point is simple. Pick three accounts from your portfolio — accounts with a lifecycle gap, flat nodes, no portfolio adoption, or where the delivery partner has already moved on. We'll run them through our model and show you exactly where the registerable pipeline is. No cost, no commitment. Just the map. Co-sell, co-grow, long-term — that's the play."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

</Deck>
